57 bool llvm::formDedicatedExitBlocks(Loop *L, DominatorTree *DT, LoopInfo *LI, 0
58 MemorySSAUpdater *MSSAU, ----
59 bool PreserveLCSSA) { ----
60 bool Changed = false; 0
61 ----
62 // We re-use a vector for the in-loop predecesosrs. ----
63 SmallVector InLoopPredecessors; 0
64 ----
65 auto RewriteExit = [&](BasicBlock *BB) { 0
66 assert(InLoopPredecessors.empty() && 0
67 "Must start with an empty predecessors list!"); ----
68 auto Cleanup = make_scope_exit([&] { InLoopPredecessors.clear(); }); 0
69 ----
70 // See if there are any non-loop predecessors of this exit block and ----
71 // keep track of the in-loop predecessors. ----
72 bool IsDedicatedExit = true; 0
73 for (auto *PredBB : predecessors(BB)) 0
74 if (L->contains(PredBB)) { 0
75 if (isa(PredBB->getTerminator())) 0
76 // We cannot rewrite exiting edges from an indirectbr. ----
77 return false; 0
78 ----
79 InLoopPredecessors.push_back(PredBB); 0
80 } else { ----
81 IsDedicatedExit = false; 0
82 } ----
83 ----
84 assert(!InLoopPredecessors.empty() && "Must have *some* loop predecessor!"); 0
85 ----
86 // Nothing to do if this is already a dedicated exit. ----
87 if (IsDedicatedExit) 0
88 return false; 0
89 ----
90 auto *NewExitBB = SplitBlockPredecessors( 0
91 BB, InLoopPredecessors, ".loopexit", DT, LI, MSSAU, PreserveLCSSA); 0
92 ----
93 if (!NewExitBB) 0
94 LLVM_DEBUG( 0
95 dbgs() << "WARNING: Can't create a dedicated exit block for loop: " ----
96 << *L << "\n"); ----
97 else ----
98 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "LoopSimplify: Creating dedicated exit block " 0
99 << NewExitBB->getName() << "\n"); ----
100 return true; 0
101 }; 0
102 ----
103 // Walk the exit blocks directly rather than building up a data structure for ----
104 // them, but only visit each one once. ----
105 SmallPtrSet Visited; 0
106 for (auto *BB : L->blocks()) 0
107 for (auto *SuccBB : successors(BB)) { 0
108 // We're looking for exit blocks so skip in-loop successors. ----
109 if (L->contains(SuccBB)) 0
110 continue; 0
111 ----
112 // Visit each exit block exactly once. ----
113 if (!Visited.insert(SuccBB).second) 0
114 continue; 0
115 ----
116 Changed |= RewriteExit(SuccBB); 0
117 } ----
118 ----
119 return Changed; 0
120 } 0

122 /// Returns the instructions that use values defined in the loop. ----
123 SmallVector llvm::findDefsUsedOutsideOfLoop(Loop *L) { 0
124 SmallVector UsedOutside; 0
125 ----
126 for (auto *Block : L->getBlocks()) 0
127 // FIXME: I believe that this could use copy_if if the Inst reference could ----
128 // be adapted into a pointer. ----
129 for (auto &Inst : *Block) { 0
130 auto Users = Inst.users(); 0
131 if (any_of(Users, [&](User *U) { 0
132 auto *Use = cast(U); 0
133 return !L->contains(Use->getParent()); 0
134 })) ----
135 UsedOutside.push_back(&Inst); 0
136 } ----
137 ----
138 return UsedOutside; 0
139 } ----

142 // By definition, all loop passes need the LoopInfo analysis and the ----
143 // Dominator tree it depends on. Because they all participate in the loop ----

155 AU.addPreservedID(LoopSimplifyID); 0

159 // which preserve lcssa form ----
160 AU.addRequired(); 0
161 AU.addPreserved(); 0
162 ----
163 // Loop passes are designed to run inside of a loop pass manager which means ----
164 // that any function analyses they require must be required by the first loop ----
165 // pass in the manager (so that it is computed before the loop pass manager ----
166 // runs) and preserved by all loop pasess in the manager. To make this ----
167 // reasonably robust, the set needed for most loop passes is maintained here. ----
168 // If your loop pass requires an analysis not listed here, you will need to ----
169 // carefully audit the loop pass manager nesting structure that results. ----
170 AU.addRequired(); 0
171 AU.addPreserved(); 0
172 AU.addPreserved(); 0
173 AU.addPreserved(); 0
174 AU.addPreserved(); 0

211 /// Set input string into loop metadata by keeping other values intact. ----
212 /// If the string is already in loop metadata update value if it is ----
213 /// different. ----
214 void llvm::addStringMetadataToLoop(Loop *TheLoop, const char *StringMD, 0
215 unsigned V) { ----
216 SmallVector MDs(1); 0
217 // If the loop already has metadata, retain it. ----
218 MDNode *LoopID = TheLoop->getLoopID(); 0
219 if (LoopID) { 0
220 for (unsigned i = 1, ie = LoopID->getNumOperands(); i < ie; ++i) { 0
221 MDNode *Node = cast(LoopID->getOperand(i)); 0
222 // If it is of form key = value, try to parse it. ----
223 if (Node->getNumOperands() == 2) { 0
224 MDString *S = dyn_cast(Node->getOperand(0)); 0
225 if (S && S->getString().equals(StringMD)) { 0
226 ConstantInt *IntMD = ----
227 mdconst::extract_or_null(Node->getOperand(1)); 0
228 if (IntMD && IntMD->getSExtValue() == V) 0
229 // It is already in place. Do nothing. ----
230 return; 0
231 // We need to update the value, so just skip it here and it will ----
232 // be added after copying other existed nodes. ----
233 continue; 0
234 } 0
235 } ----
236 MDs.push_back(Node); 0
237 } ----
238 } ----
239 // Add new metadata. ----
240 MDs.push_back(createStringMetadata(TheLoop, StringMD, V)); 0
241 // Replace current metadata node with new one. ----
242 LLVMContext &Context = TheLoop->getHeader()->getContext(); 0
243 MDNode *NewLoopID = MDNode::get(Context, MDs); 0
244 // Set operand 0 to refer to the loop id itself. ----
245 NewLoopID->replaceOperandWith(0, NewLoopID); 0
246 TheLoop->setLoopID(NewLoopID); 0
247 } 0

260 return std::nullopt; 0

263 std::optional llvm::makeFollowupLoopID( 0
264 MDNode *OrigLoopID, ArrayRef FollowupOptions, ----
265 const char *InheritOptionsExceptPrefix, bool AlwaysNew) { ----
266 if (!OrigLoopID) { 0
267 if (AlwaysNew) 0
268 return nullptr; 0
269 return std::nullopt; 0
270 } ----
271 ----
272 assert(OrigLoopID->getOperand(0) == OrigLoopID); 0
273 ----
274 bool InheritAllAttrs = !InheritOptionsExceptPrefix; 0
275 bool InheritSomeAttrs = 0
276 InheritOptionsExceptPrefix && InheritOptionsExceptPrefix[0] != '\0'; 0
277 SmallVector MDs; 0
278 MDs.push_back(nullptr); 0
279 ----
280 bool Changed = false; 0
281 if (InheritAllAttrs || InheritSomeAttrs) { 0
282 for (const MDOperand &Existing : drop_begin(OrigLoopID->operands())) { 0
283 MDNode *Op = cast(Existing.get()); 0
284 ----
285 auto InheritThisAttribute = [InheritSomeAttrs, 0
286 InheritOptionsExceptPrefix](MDNode *Op) { 0
287 if (!InheritSomeAttrs) 0
288 return false; 0
289 ----
290 // Skip malformatted attribute metadata nodes. ----
291 if (Op->getNumOperands() == 0) 0
292 return true; 0
293 Metadata *NameMD = Op->getOperand(0).get(); 0
294 if (!isa(NameMD)) 0
295 return true; 0
296 StringRef AttrName = cast(NameMD)->getString(); 0
297 ----
298 // Do not inherit excluded attributes. ----
299 return !AttrName.startswith(InheritOptionsExceptPrefix); 0
300 }; 0
301 ----
302 if (InheritThisAttribute(Op)) 0
303 MDs.push_back(Op); 0
304 else ----
305 Changed = true; 0
306 } ----
307 } else { 0
308 // Modified if we dropped at least one attribute. ----
309 Changed = OrigLoopID->getNumOperands() > 1; 0
310 } ----
311 ----
312 bool HasAnyFollowup = false; 0
313 for (StringRef OptionName : FollowupOptions) { 0
314 MDNode *FollowupNode = findOptionMDForLoopID(OrigLoopID, OptionName); 0
315 if (!FollowupNode) 0
316 continue; 0
317 ----
318 HasAnyFollowup = true; 0
319 for (const MDOperand &Option : drop_begin(FollowupNode->operands())) { 0
320 MDs.push_back(Option.get()); 0
321 Changed = true; 0
322 } ----
323 } ----
324 ----
325 // Attributes of the followup loop not specified explicity, so signal to the ----
326 // transformation pass to add suitable attributes. ----
327 if (!AlwaysNew && !HasAnyFollowup) 0
328 return std::nullopt; 0
329 ----
330 // If no attributes were added or remove, the previous loop Id can be reused. ----
331 if (!AlwaysNew && !Changed) 0
332 return OrigLoopID; 0
333 ----
334 // No attributes is equivalent to having no !llvm.loop metadata at all. ----
335 if (MDs.size() == 1) 0
336 return nullptr; 0
337 ----
338 // Build the new loop ID. ----
339 MDTuple *FollowupLoopID = MDNode::get(OrigLoopID->getContext(), MDs); 0
340 FollowupLoopID->replaceOperandWith(0, FollowupLoopID); 0
341 return FollowupLoopID; 0
342 } 0

391 TransformationMode llvm::hasVectorizeTransformation(const Loop *L) { 0
392 std::optional Enable = ----
393 getOptionalBoolLoopAttribute(L, "llvm.loop.vectorize.enable"); 0
394 ----
395 if (Enable == false) 0
396 return TM_SuppressedByUser; 0
397 ----

400 std::optional InterleaveCount = ----
401 getOptionalIntLoopAttribute(L, "llvm.loop.interleave.count"); 0
402 ----
403 // 'Forcing' vector width and interleave count to one effectively disables ----
404 // this tranformation. ----
405 if (Enable == true && VectorizeWidth && VectorizeWidth->isScalar() && 0
406 InterleaveCount == 1) 0
407 return TM_SuppressedByUser; 0
408 ----
409 if (getBooleanLoopAttribute(L, "llvm.loop.isvectorized")) 0
410 return TM_Disable; 0
411 ----
412 if (Enable == true) 0
413 return TM_ForcedByUser; 0
414 ----
415 if ((VectorizeWidth && VectorizeWidth->isScalar()) && InterleaveCount == 1) 0
416 return TM_Disable; 0
417 ----
418 if ((VectorizeWidth && VectorizeWidth->isVector()) || InterleaveCount > 1) 0
419 return TM_Enable; 0
420 ----
421 if (hasDisableAllTransformsHint(L)) 0
422 return TM_Disable; 0
423 ----
424 return TM_Unspecified; 0

447 /// Does a BFS from a given node to all of its children inside a given loop. ----
448 /// The returned vector of nodes includes the starting point. ----
449 SmallVector ----
450 llvm::collectChildrenInLoop(DomTreeNode *N, const Loop *CurLoop) { 0
451 SmallVector Worklist; 0
452 auto AddRegionToWorklist = [&](DomTreeNode *DTN) { 0
453 // Only include subregions in the top level loop. ----
454 BasicBlock *BB = DTN->getBlock(); 0
455 if (CurLoop->contains(BB)) 0
456 Worklist.push_back(DTN); 0
457 }; 0
458 ----
459 AddRegionToWorklist(N); 0
460 ----
461 for (size_t I = 0; I < Worklist.size(); I++) { 0
462 for (DomTreeNode *Child : Worklist[I]->children()) 0
463 AddRegionToWorklist(Child); 0
464 } ----
465 ----
466 return Worklist; 0
467 } ----

469 bool llvm::isAlmostDeadIV(PHINode *PN, BasicBlock *LatchBlock, Value *Cond) { 0
470 int LatchIdx = PN->getBasicBlockIndex(LatchBlock); 0
471 Value *IncV = PN->getIncomingValue(LatchIdx); 0
472 ----
473 for (User *U : PN->users()) 0
474 if (U != Cond && U != IncV) return false; 0
475 ----
476 for (User *U : IncV->users()) 0
477 if (U != Cond && U != PN) return false; 0
478 return true; 0
479 } ----

482 void llvm::deleteDeadLoop(Loop *L, DominatorTree *DT, ScalarEvolution *SE, 0
483 LoopInfo *LI, MemorySSA *MSSA) { ----
484 assert((!DT || L->isLCSSAForm(*DT)) && "Expected LCSSA!"); 0
485 auto *Preheader = L->getLoopPreheader(); 0
486 assert(Preheader && "Preheader should exist!"); 0
487 ----
488 std::unique_ptr MSSAU; 0
489 if (MSSA) 0
490 MSSAU = std::make_unique(MSSA); 0
491 ----
492 // Now that we know the removal is safe, remove the loop by changing the ----
493 // branch from the preheader to go to the single exit block. ----
494 // ----
495 // Because we're deleting a large chunk of code at once, the sequence in which ----
496 // we remove things is very important to avoid invalidation issues. ----
497 ----
498 // Tell ScalarEvolution that the loop is deleted. Do this before ----
499 // deleting the loop so that ScalarEvolution can look at the loop ----
500 // to determine what it needs to clean up. ----
501 if (SE) { 0
502 SE->forgetLoop(L); 0
503 SE->forgetBlockAndLoopDispositions(); 0
504 } ----
505 ----
506 Instruction *OldTerm = Preheader->getTerminator(); 0
507 assert(!OldTerm->mayHaveSideEffects() && 0
508 "Preheader must end with a side-effect-free terminator"); ----
509 assert(OldTerm->getNumSuccessors() == 1 && 0
510 "Preheader must have a single successor"); ----
511 // Connect the preheader to the exit block. Keep the old edge to the header ----
512 // around to perform the dominator tree update in two separate steps ----
513 // -- #1 insertion of the edge preheader -> exit and #2 deletion of the edge ----
514 // preheader -> header. ----
515 // ----
516 // ----
517 // 0. Preheader 1. Preheader 2. Preheader ----
518 // | | | | ----
519 // V | V | ----
520 // Header <--\ | Header <--\ | Header <--\ ----
521 // | | | | | | | | | | | ----
522 // | V | | | V | | | V | ----
523 // | Body --/ | | Body --/ | | Body --/ ----
524 // V V V V V ----
525 // Exit Exit Exit ----
526 // ----
527 // By doing this is two separate steps we can perform the dominator tree ----
528 // update without using the batch update API. ----
529 // ----
530 // Even when the loop is never executed, we cannot remove the edge from the ----
531 // source block to the exit block. Consider the case where the unexecuted loop ----
532 // branches back to an outer loop. If we deleted the loop and removed the edge ----
533 // coming to this inner loop, this will break the outer loop structure (by ----
534 // deleting the backedge of the outer loop). If the outer loop is indeed a ----
535 // non-loop, it will be deleted in a future iteration of loop deletion pass. ----
536 IRBuilder<> Builder(OldTerm); 0
537 ----
538 auto *ExitBlock = L->getUniqueExitBlock(); 0
539 DomTreeUpdater DTU(DT, DomTreeUpdater::UpdateStrategy::Eager); 0
540 if (ExitBlock) { 0
541 assert(ExitBlock && "Should have a unique exit block!"); 0
542 assert(L->hasDedicatedExits() && "Loop should have dedicated exits!"); 0
543 ----
544 Builder.CreateCondBr(Builder.getFalse(), L->getHeader(), ExitBlock); 0
545 // Remove the old branch. The conditional branch becomes a new terminator. ----
546 OldTerm->eraseFromParent(); 0
547 ----
548 // Rewrite phis in the exit block to get their inputs from the Preheader ----
549 // instead of the exiting block. ----
550 for (PHINode &P : ExitBlock->phis()) { 0
551 // Set the zero'th element of Phi to be from the preheader and remove all ----
552 // other incoming values. Given the loop has dedicated exits, all other ----
553 // incoming values must be from the exiting blocks. ----
554 int PredIndex = 0; 0
555 P.setIncomingBlock(PredIndex, Preheader); 0
556 // Removes all incoming values from all other exiting blocks (including ----
557 // duplicate values from an exiting block). ----
558 // Nuke all entries except the zero'th entry which is the preheader entry. ----
559 // NOTE! We need to remove Incoming Values in the reverse order as done ----
560 // below, to keep the indices valid for deletion (removeIncomingValues ----
561 // updates getNumIncomingValues and shifts all values down into the ----
562 // operand being deleted). ----
563 for (unsigned i = 0, e = P.getNumIncomingValues() - 1; i != e; ++i) 0
564 P.removeIncomingValue(e - i, false); 0
565 ----
566 assert((P.getNumIncomingValues() == 1 && 0
567 P.getIncomingBlock(PredIndex) == Preheader) && ----
568 "Should have exactly one value and that's from the preheader!"); ----
569 } ----
570 ----
571 if (DT) { 0
572 DTU.applyUpdates({{DominatorTree::Insert, Preheader, ExitBlock}}); 0
573 if (MSSA) { 0
574 MSSAU->applyUpdates({{DominatorTree::Insert, Preheader, ExitBlock}}, 0
575 *DT); ----
576 if (VerifyMemorySSA) 0
577 MSSA->verifyMemorySSA(); 0
578 } ----
579 } ----
580 ----
581 // Disconnect the loop body by branching directly to its exit. ----
582 Builder.SetInsertPoint(Preheader->getTerminator()); 0
583 Builder.CreateBr(ExitBlock); 0
584 // Remove the old branch. ----
585 Preheader->getTerminator()->eraseFromParent(); 0
586 } else { ----
587 assert(L->hasNoExitBlocks() && 0
588 "Loop should have either zero or one exit blocks."); ----
589 ----
590 Builder.SetInsertPoint(OldTerm); 0
591 Builder.CreateUnreachable(); 0
592 Preheader->getTerminator()->eraseFromParent(); 0
593 } ----
594 ----
595 if (DT) { 0
596 DTU.applyUpdates({{DominatorTree::Delete, Preheader, L->getHeader()}}); 0
597 if (MSSA) { 0
598 MSSAU->applyUpdates({{DominatorTree::Delete, Preheader, L->getHeader()}}, 0
599 *DT); ----
600 SmallSetVector DeadBlockSet(L->block_begin(), ----
601 L->block_end()); 0
602 MSSAU->removeBlocks(DeadBlockSet); 0
603 if (VerifyMemorySSA) 0
604 MSSA->verifyMemorySSA(); 0
605 } 0
606 } ----
607 ----
608 // Use a map to unique and a vector to guarantee deterministic ordering. ----
609 llvm::SmallDenseSet DeadDebugSet; 0
610 llvm::SmallVector DeadDebugInst; 0
611 ----
612 if (ExitBlock) { 0
613 // Given LCSSA form is satisfied, we should not have users of instructions ----
614 // within the dead loop outside of the loop. However, LCSSA doesn't take ----
615 // unreachable uses into account. We handle them here. ----
616 // We could do it after drop all references (in this case all users in the ----
617 // loop will be already eliminated and we have less work to do but according ----
618 // to API doc of User::dropAllReferences only valid operation after dropping ----
619 // references, is deletion. So let's substitute all usages of ----
620 // instruction from the loop with poison value of corresponding type first. ----
621 for (auto *Block : L->blocks()) 0
622 for (Instruction &I : *Block) { 0
623 auto *Poison = PoisonValue::get(I.getType()); 0
624 for (Use &U : llvm::make_early_inc_range(I.uses())) { 0
625 if (auto *Usr = dyn_cast(U.getUser())) 0
626 if (L->contains(Usr->getParent())) 0
627 continue; 0
628 // If we have a DT then we can check that uses outside a loop only in ----
629 // unreachable block. ----
630 if (DT) 0
631 assert(!DT->isReachableFromEntry(U) && 0
632 "Unexpected user in reachable block"); ----
633 U.set(Poison); 0
634 } ----
635 auto *DVI = dyn_cast(&I); 0
636 if (!DVI) 0
637 continue; 0
638 if (!DeadDebugSet.insert(DebugVariable(DVI)).second) 0
639 continue; 0
640 DeadDebugInst.push_back(DVI); 0
641 } ----
642 ----
643 // After the loop has been deleted all the values defined and modified ----
644 // inside the loop are going to be unavailable. Values computed in the ----
645 // loop will have been deleted, automatically causing their debug uses ----
646 // be be replaced with undef. Loop invariant values will still be available. ----
647 // Move dbg.values out the loop so that earlier location ranges are still ----
648 // terminated and loop invariant assignments are preserved. ----
649 Instruction *InsertDbgValueBefore = ExitBlock->getFirstNonPHI(); 0
650 assert(InsertDbgValueBefore && 0
651 "There should be a non-PHI instruction in exit block, else these " ----
652 "instructions will have no parent."); ----
653 for (auto *DVI : DeadDebugInst) 0
654 DVI->moveBefore(InsertDbgValueBefore); 0
655 } ----
656 ----
657 // Remove the block from the reference counting scheme, so that we can ----
658 // delete it freely later. ----
659 for (auto *Block : L->blocks()) 0
660 Block->dropAllReferences(); 0
661 ----
662 if (MSSA && VerifyMemorySSA) 0
663 MSSA->verifyMemorySSA(); 0
664 ----
665 if (LI) { 0
666 // Erase the instructions and the blocks without having to worry ----
667 // about ordering because we already dropped the references. ----
668 // NOTE: This iteration is safe because erasing the block does not remove ----
669 // its entry from the loop's block list. We do that in the next section. ----
670 for (BasicBlock *BB : L->blocks()) 0
671 BB->eraseFromParent(); 0
672 ----
673 // Finally, the blocks from loopinfo. This has to happen late because ----
674 // otherwise our loop iterators won't work. ----
675 ----
676 SmallPtrSet blocks; 0
677 blocks.insert(L->block_begin(), L->block_end()); 0
678 for (BasicBlock *BB : blocks) 0
679 LI->removeBlock(BB); 0
680 ----
681 // The last step is to update LoopInfo now that we've eliminated this loop. ----
682 // Note: LoopInfo::erase remove the given loop and relink its subloops with ----
683 // its parent. While removeLoop/removeChildLoop remove the given loop but ----
684 // not relink its subloops, which is what we want. ----
685 if (Loop *ParentLoop = L->getParentLoop()) { 0
686 Loop::iterator I = find(*ParentLoop, L); 0
687 assert(I != ParentLoop->end() && "Couldn't find loop"); 0
688 ParentLoop->removeChildLoop(I); 0
689 } else { ----
690 Loop::iterator I = find(*LI, L); 0
691 assert(I != LI->end() && "Couldn't find loop"); 0
692 LI->removeLoop(I); 0
693 } ----
694 LI->destroy(L); 0
695 } 0
696 } 0
697 ----
698 void llvm::breakLoopBackedge(Loop *L, DominatorTree &DT, ScalarEvolution &SE, 0
699 LoopInfo &LI, MemorySSA *MSSA) { ----
700 auto *Latch = L->getLoopLatch(); 0
701 assert(Latch && "multiple latches not yet supported"); 0
702 auto *Header = L->getHeader(); 0
703 Loop *OutermostLoop = L->getOutermostLoop(); 0
704 ----
705 SE.forgetLoop(L); 0
706 SE.forgetBlockAndLoopDispositions(); 0
707 ----
708 std::unique_ptr MSSAU; 0
709 if (MSSA) 0
710 MSSAU = std::make_unique(MSSA); 0
711 ----
712 // Update the CFG and domtree. We chose to special case a couple of ----
713 // of common cases for code quality and test readability reasons. ----
714 [&]() -> void { 0
715 if (auto *BI = dyn_cast(Latch->getTerminator())) { 0
716 if (!BI->isConditional()) { 0
717 DomTreeUpdater DTU(&DT, DomTreeUpdater::UpdateStrategy::Eager); 0
718 (void)changeToUnreachable(BI, /*PreserveLCSSA*/ true, &DTU, 0
719 MSSAU.get()); 0
720 return; 0
721 } 0
722 ----
723 // Conditional latch/exit - note that latch can be shared by inner ----
724 // and outer loop so the other target doesn't need to an exit ----
725 if (L->isLoopExiting(Latch)) { 0
726 // TODO: Generalize ConstantFoldTerminator so that it can be used ----
727 // here without invalidating LCSSA or MemorySSA. (Tricky case for ----
728 // LCSSA: header is an exit block of a preceeding sibling loop w/o ----
729 // dedicated exits.) ----
730 const unsigned ExitIdx = L->contains(BI->getSuccessor(0)) ? 1 : 0; 0
731 BasicBlock *ExitBB = BI->getSuccessor(ExitIdx); 0
732 ----
733 DomTreeUpdater DTU(&DT, DomTreeUpdater::UpdateStrategy::Eager); 0
734 Header->removePredecessor(Latch, true); 0
735 ----
736 IRBuilder<> Builder(BI); 0
737 auto *NewBI = Builder.CreateBr(ExitBB); 0
738 // Transfer the metadata to the new branch instruction (minus the ----
739 // loop info since this is no longer a loop) ----
740 NewBI->copyMetadata(*BI, {LLVMContext::MD_dbg, 0
741 LLVMContext::MD_annotation}); ----
742 ----
743 BI->eraseFromParent(); 0
744 DTU.applyUpdates({{DominatorTree::Delete, Latch, Header}}); 0
745 if (MSSA) 0
746 MSSAU->applyUpdates({{DominatorTree::Delete, Latch, Header}}, DT); 0
747 return; 0
748 } 0
749 } ----
750 ----
751 // General case. By splitting the backedge, and then explicitly making it ----
752 // unreachable we gracefully handle corner cases such as switch and invoke ----
753 // termiantors. ----
754 auto *BackedgeBB = SplitEdge(Latch, Header, &DT, &LI, MSSAU.get()); 0
755 ----
756 DomTreeUpdater DTU(&DT, DomTreeUpdater::UpdateStrategy::Eager); 0
757 (void)changeToUnreachable(BackedgeBB->getTerminator(), 0
758 /*PreserveLCSSA*/ true, &DTU, MSSAU.get()); ----
759 }(); 0
760 ----
761 // Erase (and destroy) this loop instance. Handles relinking sub-loops ----
762 // and blocks within the loop as needed. ----
763 LI.erase(L); 0
764 ----
765 // If the loop we broke had a parent, then changeToUnreachable might have ----
766 // caused a block to be removed from the parent loop (see loop_nest_lcssa ----
767 // test case in zero-btc.ll for an example), thus changing the parent's ----
768 // exit blocks. If that happened, we need to rebuild LCSSA on the outermost ----
769 // loop which might have a had a block removed. ----
770 if (OutermostLoop != L) 0
771 formLCSSARecursively(*OutermostLoop, DT, &LI, &SE); 0
772 } 0
773 ----
774 ----
775 /// Checks if \p L has an exiting latch branch. There may also be other ----
776 /// exiting blocks. Returns branch instruction terminating the loop ----
777 /// latch if above check is successful, nullptr otherwise. ----
778 static BranchInst *getExpectedExitLoopLatchBranch(Loop *L) { 0
779 BasicBlock *Latch = L->getLoopLatch(); 0
780 if (!Latch) 0
781 return nullptr; 0
782 ----
783 BranchInst *LatchBR = dyn_cast(Latch->getTerminator()); 0
784 if (!LatchBR || LatchBR->getNumSuccessors() != 2 || !L->isLoopExiting(Latch)) 0
785 return nullptr; 0
786 ----
787 assert((LatchBR->getSuccessor(0) == L->getHeader() || 0
788 LatchBR->getSuccessor(1) == L->getHeader()) && ----
789 "At least one edge out of the latch must go to the header"); ----
790 ----
791 return LatchBR; 0
792 } ----
793 ----
794 /// Return the estimated trip count for any exiting branch which dominates ----
795 /// the loop latch. ----
796 static std::optional getEstimatedTripCount(BranchInst *ExitingBranch, 0
797 Loop *L, ----
798 uint64_t &OrigExitWeight) { ----
799 // To estimate the number of times the loop body was executed, we want to ----
800 // know the number of times the backedge was taken, vs. the number of times ----
801 // we exited the loop. ----
802 uint64_t LoopWeight, ExitWeight; ----
803 if (!extractBranchWeights(*ExitingBranch, LoopWeight, ExitWeight)) 0
804 return std::nullopt; 0
805 ----
806 if (L->contains(ExitingBranch->getSuccessor(1))) 0
807 std::swap(LoopWeight, ExitWeight); 0
808 ----
809 if (!ExitWeight) 0
810 // Don't have a way to return predicated infinite ----
811 return std::nullopt; 0
812 ----
813 OrigExitWeight = ExitWeight; 0
814 ----
815 // Estimated exit count is a ratio of the loop weight by the weight of the ----
816 // edge exiting the loop, rounded to nearest. ----
817 uint64_t ExitCount = llvm::divideNearest(LoopWeight, ExitWeight); 0
818 // Estimated trip count is one plus estimated exit count. ----
819 return ExitCount + 1; 0
820 } ----
821 ----
822 std::optional ----
823 llvm::getLoopEstimatedTripCount(Loop *L, 0
824 unsigned *EstimatedLoopInvocationWeight) { ----
825 // Currently we take the estimate exit count only from the loop latch, ----
826 // ignoring other exiting blocks. This can overestimate the trip count ----
827 // if we exit through another exit, but can never underestimate it. ----
828 // TODO: incorporate information from other exits ----
829 if (BranchInst *LatchBranch = getExpectedExitLoopLatchBranch(L)) { 0
830 uint64_t ExitWeight; ----
831 if (std::optional EstTripCount = 0
832 getEstimatedTripCount(LatchBranch, L, ExitWeight)) { 0
833 if (EstimatedLoopInvocationWeight) 0
834 *EstimatedLoopInvocationWeight = ExitWeight; 0
835 return *EstTripCount; 0
836 } ----
837 } ----
838 return std::nullopt; 0
839 } ----
840 ----
841 bool llvm::setLoopEstimatedTripCount(Loop *L, unsigned EstimatedTripCount, 0
842 unsigned EstimatedloopInvocationWeight) { ----
843 // At the moment, we currently support changing the estimate trip count of ----
844 // the latch branch only. We could extend this API to manipulate estimated ----
845 // trip counts for any exit. ----
846 BranchInst *LatchBranch = getExpectedExitLoopLatchBranch(L); 0
847 if (!LatchBranch) 0
848 return false; 0
849 ----
850 // Calculate taken and exit weights. ----
851 unsigned LatchExitWeight = 0; 0
852 unsigned BackedgeTakenWeight = 0; 0
853 ----
854 if (EstimatedTripCount > 0) { 0
855 LatchExitWeight = EstimatedloopInvocationWeight; 0
856 BackedgeTakenWeight = (EstimatedTripCount - 1) * LatchExitWeight; 0
857 } ----
858 ----
859 // Make a swap if back edge is taken when condition is "false". ----
860 if (LatchBranch->getSuccessor(0) != L->getHeader()) 0
861 std::swap(BackedgeTakenWeight, LatchExitWeight); 0
862 ----
863 MDBuilder MDB(LatchBranch->getContext()); 0
864 ----
865 // Set/Update profile metadata. ----
866 LatchBranch->setMetadata( 0
867 LLVMContext::MD_prof, ----
868 MDB.createBranchWeights(BackedgeTakenWeight, LatchExitWeight)); ----
869 ----
870 return true; 0
871 } ----
872 ----
873 bool llvm::hasIterationCountInvariantInParent(Loop *InnerLoop, 0
874 ScalarEvolution &SE) { ----
875 Loop *OuterL = InnerLoop->getParentLoop(); 0
876 if (!OuterL) 0
877 return true; 0
878 ----
879 // Get the backedge taken count for the inner loop ----
880 BasicBlock *InnerLoopLatch = InnerLoop->getLoopLatch(); 0
881 const SCEV *InnerLoopBECountSC = SE.getExitCount(InnerLoop, InnerLoopLatch); 0
882 if (isa(InnerLoopBECountSC) || 0
883 !InnerLoopBECountSC->getType()->isIntegerTy()) 0
884 return false; 0
885 ----
886 // Get whether count is invariant to the outer loop ----
887 ScalarEvolution::LoopDisposition LD = ----
888 SE.getLoopDisposition(InnerLoopBECountSC, OuterL); 0
889 if (LD != ScalarEvolution::LoopInvariant) 0
890 return false; 0
891 ----
892 return true; 0
893 } ----
894 ----
895 Intrinsic::ID llvm::getMinMaxReductionIntrinsicOp(RecurKind RK) { 0
896 switch (RK) { 0
897 default: 0
898 llvm_unreachable("Unknown min/max recurrence kind"); 0
899 case RecurKind::UMin: 0
900 return Intrinsic::umin; 0
901 case RecurKind::UMax: 0
902 return Intrinsic::umax; 0
903 case RecurKind::SMin: 0
904 return Intrinsic::smin; 0
905 case RecurKind::SMax: 0
906 return Intrinsic::smax; 0
907 case RecurKind::FMin: 0
908 return Intrinsic::minnum; 0
909 case RecurKind::FMax: 0
910 return Intrinsic::maxnum; 0
911 case RecurKind::FMinimum: 0
912 return Intrinsic::minimum; 0
913 case RecurKind::FMaximum: 0
914 return Intrinsic::maximum; 0
915 } ----
916 } ----
917 ----
918 CmpInst::Predicate llvm::getMinMaxReductionPredicate(RecurKind RK) { 0
919 switch (RK) { 0
920 default: 0
921 llvm_unreachable("Unknown min/max recurrence kind"); 0
922 case RecurKind::UMin: 0
923 return CmpInst::ICMP_ULT; 0
924 case RecurKind::UMax: 0
925 return CmpInst::ICMP_UGT; 0
926 case RecurKind::SMin: 0
927 return CmpInst::ICMP_SLT; 0
928 case RecurKind::SMax: 0
929 return CmpInst::ICMP_SGT; 0
930 case RecurKind::FMin: 0
931 return CmpInst::FCMP_OLT; 0
932 case RecurKind::FMax: 0
933 return CmpInst::FCMP_OGT; 0
934 // We do not add FMinimum/FMaximum recurrence kind here since there is no ----
935 // equivalent predicate which compares signed zeroes according to the ----
936 // semantics of the intrinsics (llvm.minimum/maximum). ----
937 } ----
938 } ----
939 ----
940 Value *llvm::createSelectCmpOp(IRBuilderBase &Builder, Value *StartVal, 0
941 RecurKind RK, Value *Left, Value *Right) { ----
942 if (auto VTy = dyn_cast(Left->getType())) 0
943 StartVal = Builder.CreateVectorSplat(VTy->getElementCount(), StartVal); 0
944 Value *Cmp = ----
945 Builder.CreateCmp(CmpInst::ICMP_NE, Left, StartVal, "rdx.select.cmp"); 0
946 return Builder.CreateSelect(Cmp, Left, Right, "rdx.select"); 0
947 } ----
948 ----
949 Value *llvm::createMinMaxOp(IRBuilderBase &Builder, RecurKind RK, Value *Left, 0
950 Value *Right) { ----
951 Type *Ty = Left->getType(); 0
952 if (Ty->isIntOrIntVectorTy() || 0
953 (RK == RecurKind::FMinimum || RK == RecurKind::FMaximum)) { 0
954 // TODO: Add float minnum/maxnum support when FMF nnan is set. ----
955 Intrinsic::ID Id = getMinMaxReductionIntrinsicOp(RK); 0
956 return Builder.CreateIntrinsic(Ty, Id, {Left, Right}, nullptr, 0
957 "rdx.minmax"); 0
958 } ----
959 CmpInst::Predicate Pred = getMinMaxReductionPredicate(RK); 0
960 Value *Cmp = Builder.CreateCmp(Pred, Left, Right, "rdx.minmax.cmp"); 0
961 Value *Select = Builder.CreateSelect(Cmp, Left, Right, "rdx.minmax.select"); 0
962 return Select; 0
963 } ----
964 ----
965 // Helper to generate an ordered reduction. ----
966 Value *llvm::getOrderedReduction(IRBuilderBase &Builder, Value *Acc, Value *Src, 0
967 unsigned Op, RecurKind RdxKind) { ----
968 unsigned VF = cast(Src->getType())->getNumElements(); 0
969 ----
970 // Extract and apply reduction ops in ascending order: ----
971 // e.g. ((((Acc + Scl[0]) + Scl[1]) + Scl[2]) + ) ... + Scl[VF-1] ----
972 Value *Result = Acc; 0
973 for (unsigned ExtractIdx = 0; ExtractIdx != VF; ++ExtractIdx) { 0
974 Value *Ext = ----
975 Builder.CreateExtractElement(Src, Builder.getInt32(ExtractIdx)); 0
976 ----
977 if (Op != Instruction::ICmp && Op != Instruction::FCmp) { 0
978 Result = Builder.CreateBinOp((Instruction::BinaryOps)Op, Result, Ext, 0
979 "bin.rdx"); ----
980 } else { ----
981 assert(RecurrenceDescriptor::isMinMaxRecurrenceKind(RdxKind) && 0
982 "Invalid min/max"); ----
983 Result = createMinMaxOp(Builder, RdxKind, Result, Ext); 0
984 } ----
985 } ----
986 ----
987 return Result; 0
988 } ----
989 ----
990 // Helper to generate a log2 shuffle reduction. ----
991 Value *llvm::getShuffleReduction(IRBuilderBase &Builder, Value *Src, 0
992 unsigned Op, RecurKind RdxKind) { ----
993 unsigned VF = cast(Src->getType())->getNumElements(); 0
994 // VF is a power of 2 so we can emit the reduction using log2(VF) shuffles ----
995 // and vector ops, reducing the set of values being computed by half each ----
996 // round. ----
997 assert(isPowerOf2_32(VF) && 0
998 "Reduction emission only supported for pow2 vectors!"); ----
999 // Note: fast-math-flags flags are controlled by the builder configuration ----
1000 // and are assumed to apply to all generated arithmetic instructions. Other ----
1001 // poison generating flags (nsw/nuw/inbounds/inrange/exact) are not part ----
1002 // of the builder configuration, and since they're not passed explicitly, ----
1003 // will never be relevant here. Note that it would be generally unsound to ----
1004 // propagate these from an intrinsic call to the expansion anyways as we/ ----
1005 // change the order of operations. ----
1006 Value *TmpVec = Src; 0
1007 SmallVector ShuffleMask(VF); 0
1008 for (unsigned i = VF; i != 1; i >>= 1) { 0
1009 // Move the upper half of the vector to the lower half. ----
1010 for (unsigned j = 0; j != i / 2; ++j) 0
1011 ShuffleMask[j] = i / 2 + j; 0
1012 ----
1013 // Fill the rest of the mask with undef. ----
1014 std::fill(&ShuffleMask[i / 2], ShuffleMask.end(), -1); 0
1015 ----
1016 Value *Shuf = Builder.CreateShuffleVector(TmpVec, ShuffleMask, "rdx.shuf"); 0
1017 ----
1018 if (Op != Instruction::ICmp && Op != Instruction::FCmp) { 0
1019 TmpVec = Builder.CreateBinOp((Instruction::BinaryOps)Op, TmpVec, Shuf, 0
1020 "bin.rdx"); ----
1021 } else { ----
1022 assert(RecurrenceDescriptor::isMinMaxRecurrenceKind(RdxKind) && 0
1023 "Invalid min/max"); ----
1024 TmpVec = createMinMaxOp(Builder, RdxKind, TmpVec, Shuf); 0
1025 } ----
1026 } ----
1027 // The result is in the first element of the vector. ----
1028 return Builder.CreateExtractElement(TmpVec, Builder.getInt32(0)); 0
1029 } 0
1030 ----
1031 Value *llvm::createSelectCmpTargetReduction(IRBuilderBase &Builder, 0
1032 const TargetTransformInfo *TTI, ----
1033 Value *Src, ----
1034 const RecurrenceDescriptor &Desc, ----
1035 PHINode *OrigPhi) { ----
1036 assert(RecurrenceDescriptor::isSelectCmpRecurrenceKind( 0
1037 Desc.getRecurrenceKind()) && ----
1038 "Unexpected reduction kind"); ----
1039 Value *InitVal = Desc.getRecurrenceStartValue(); 0
1040 Value *NewVal = nullptr; 0
1041 ----
1042 // First use the original phi to determine the new value we're trying to ----
1043 // select from in the loop. ----
1044 SelectInst *SI = nullptr; 0
1045 for (auto *U : OrigPhi->users()) { 0
1046 if ((SI = dyn_cast(U))) 0
1047 break; 0
1048 } ----
1049 assert(SI && "One user of the original phi should be a select"); 0
1050 ----
1051 if (SI->getTrueValue() == OrigPhi) 0
1052 NewVal = SI->getFalseValue(); 0
1053 else { ----
1054 assert(SI->getFalseValue() == OrigPhi && 0
1055 "At least one input to the select should be the original Phi"); ----
1056 NewVal = SI->getTrueValue(); 0
1057 } ----
1058 ----
1059 // Create a splat vector with the new value and compare this to the vector ----
1060 // we want to reduce. ----
1061 ElementCount EC = cast(Src->getType())->getElementCount(); 0
1062 Value *Right = Builder.CreateVectorSplat(EC, InitVal); 0
1063 Value *Cmp = ----
1064 Builder.CreateCmp(CmpInst::ICMP_NE, Src, Right, "rdx.select.cmp"); 0
1065 ----
1066 // If any predicate is true it means that we want to select the new value. ----
1067 Cmp = Builder.CreateOrReduce(Cmp); 0
1068 return Builder.CreateSelect(Cmp, NewVal, InitVal, "rdx.select"); 0
1069 } ----
1070 ----
1071 Value *llvm::createSimpleTargetReduction(IRBuilderBase &Builder, 0
1072 const TargetTransformInfo *TTI, ----
1073 Value *Src, RecurKind RdxKind) { ----
1074 auto *SrcVecEltTy = cast(Src->getType())->getElementType(); 0
1075 switch (RdxKind) { 0
1076 case RecurKind::Add: 0
1077 return Builder.CreateAddReduce(Src); 0
1078 case RecurKind::Mul: 0
1079 return Builder.CreateMulReduce(Src); 0
1080 case RecurKind::And: 0
1081 return Builder.CreateAndReduce(Src); 0
1082 case RecurKind::Or: 0
1083 return Builder.CreateOrReduce(Src); 0
1084 case RecurKind::Xor: 0
1085 return Builder.CreateXorReduce(Src); 0
1086 case RecurKind::FMulAdd: 0
1087 case RecurKind::FAdd: ----
1088 return Builder.CreateFAddReduce(ConstantFP::getNegativeZero(SrcVecEltTy), 0
1089 Src); 0
1090 case RecurKind::FMul: 0
1091 return Builder.CreateFMulReduce(ConstantFP::get(SrcVecEltTy, 1.0), Src); 0
1092 case RecurKind::SMax: 0
1093 return Builder.CreateIntMaxReduce(Src, true); 0
1094 case RecurKind::SMin: 0
1095 return Builder.CreateIntMinReduce(Src, true); 0
1096 case RecurKind::UMax: 0
1097 return Builder.CreateIntMaxReduce(Src, false); 0
1098 case RecurKind::UMin: 0
1099 return Builder.CreateIntMinReduce(Src, false); 0
1100 case RecurKind::FMax: 0
1101 return Builder.CreateFPMaxReduce(Src); 0
1102 case RecurKind::FMin: 0
1103 return Builder.CreateFPMinReduce(Src); 0
1104 case RecurKind::FMinimum: 0
1105 return Builder.CreateFPMinimumReduce(Src); 0
1106 case RecurKind::FMaximum: 0
1107 return Builder.CreateFPMaximumReduce(Src); 0
1108 default: 0
1109 llvm_unreachable("Unhandled opcode"); 0
1110 } ----
1111 } ----
1112 ----
1113 Value *llvm::createTargetReduction(IRBuilderBase &B, 0
1114 const TargetTransformInfo *TTI, ----
1115 const RecurrenceDescriptor &Desc, Value *Src, ----
1116 PHINode *OrigPhi) { ----
1117 // TODO: Support in-order reductions based on the recurrence descriptor. ----
1118 // All ops in the reduction inherit fast-math-flags from the recurrence ----
1119 // descriptor. ----
1120 IRBuilderBase::FastMathFlagGuard FMFGuard(B); 0
1121 B.setFastMathFlags(Desc.getFastMathFlags()); 0
1122 ----
1123 RecurKind RK = Desc.getRecurrenceKind(); 0
1124 if (RecurrenceDescriptor::isSelectCmpRecurrenceKind(RK)) 0
1125 return createSelectCmpTargetReduction(B, TTI, Src, Desc, OrigPhi); 0
1126 ----
1127 return createSimpleTargetReduction(B, TTI, Src, RK); 0
1128 } 0
1129 ----
1130 Value *llvm::createOrderedReduction(IRBuilderBase &B, 0
1131 const RecurrenceDescriptor &Desc, ----
1132 Value *Src, Value *Start) { ----
1133 assert((Desc.getRecurrenceKind() == RecurKind::FAdd || 0
1134 Desc.getRecurrenceKind() == RecurKind::FMulAdd) && ----
1135 "Unexpected reduction kind"); ----
1136 assert(Src->getType()->isVectorTy() && "Expected a vector type"); 0
1137 assert(!Start->getType()->isVectorTy() && "Expected a scalar type"); 0
1138 ----
1139 return B.CreateFAddReduce(Start, Src); 0
1140 } ----
1141 ----
1142 void llvm::propagateIRFlags(Value *I, ArrayRef VL, Value *OpValue, 0
1143 bool IncludeWrapFlags) { ----
1144 auto *VecOp = dyn_cast(I); 0
1145 if (!VecOp) 0
1146 return; 0
1147 auto *Intersection = (OpValue == nullptr) ? dyn_cast(VL[0]) 0
1148 : dyn_cast(OpValue); 0
1149 if (!Intersection) 0
1150 return; 0
1151 const unsigned Opcode = Intersection->getOpcode(); 0
1152 VecOp->copyIRFlags(Intersection, IncludeWrapFlags); 0
1153 for (auto *V : VL) { 0
1154 auto *Instr = dyn_cast(V); 0
1155 if (!Instr) 0
1156 continue; 0
1157 if (OpValue == nullptr || Opcode == Instr->getOpcode()) 0
1158 VecOp->andIRFlags(V); 0
1159 } ----
1160 } ----
1161 ----
1162 bool llvm::isKnownNegativeInLoop(const SCEV *S, const Loop *L, 0
1163 ScalarEvolution &SE) { ----
1164 const SCEV *Zero = SE.getZero(S->getType()); 0
1165 return SE.isAvailableAtLoopEntry(S, L) && 0
1166 SE.isLoopEntryGuardedByCond(L, ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT, S, Zero); 0
1167 } ----
1168 ----
1169 bool llvm::isKnownNonNegativeInLoop(const SCEV *S, const Loop *L, 0
1170 ScalarEvolution &SE) { ----
1171 const SCEV *Zero = SE.getZero(S->getType()); 0
1172 return SE.isAvailableAtLoopEntry(S, L) && 0
1173 SE.isLoopEntryGuardedByCond(L, ICmpInst::ICMP_SGE, S, Zero); 0
1174 } ----
1175 ----
1176 bool llvm::isKnownPositiveInLoop(const SCEV *S, const Loop *L, 0
1177 ScalarEvolution &SE) { ----
1178 const SCEV *Zero = SE.getZero(S->getType()); 0
1179 return SE.isAvailableAtLoopEntry(S, L) && 0
1180 SE.isLoopEntryGuardedByCond(L, ICmpInst::ICMP_SGT, S, Zero); 0
1181 } ----
1182 ----
1183 bool llvm::isKnownNonPositiveInLoop(const SCEV *S, const Loop *L, 0
1184 ScalarEvolution &SE) { ----
1185 const SCEV *Zero = SE.getZero(S->getType()); 0
1186 return SE.isAvailableAtLoopEntry(S, L) && 0
1187 SE.isLoopEntryGuardedByCond(L, ICmpInst::ICMP_SLE, S, Zero); 0
1188 } ----
1189 ----
1190 bool llvm::cannotBeMinInLoop(const SCEV *S, const Loop *L, ScalarEvolution &SE, 0
1191 bool Signed) { ----
1192 unsigned BitWidth = cast(S->getType())->getBitWidth(); 0
1193 APInt Min = Signed ? APInt::getSignedMinValue(BitWidth) : ----
1194 APInt::getMinValue(BitWidth); 0
1195 auto Predicate = Signed ? ICmpInst::ICMP_SGT : ICmpInst::ICMP_UGT; 0
1196 return SE.isAvailableAtLoopEntry(S, L) && 0
1197 SE.isLoopEntryGuardedByCond(L, Predicate, S, 0
1198 SE.getConstant(Min)); 0
1199 } 0
1200 ----
1201 bool llvm::cannotBeMaxInLoop(const SCEV *S, const Loop *L, ScalarEvolution &SE, 0
1202 bool Signed) { ----
1203 unsigned BitWidth = cast(S->getType())->getBitWidth(); 0
1204 APInt Max = Signed ? APInt::getSignedMaxValue(BitWidth) : ----
1205 APInt::getMaxValue(BitWidth); 0
1206 auto Predicate = Signed ? ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT : ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT; 0
1207 return SE.isAvailableAtLoopEntry(S, L) && 0
1208 SE.isLoopEntryGuardedByCond(L, Predicate, S, 0
1209 SE.getConstant(Max)); 0
1210 } 0
1211 ----
1212 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
1213 // rewriteLoopExitValues - Optimize IV users outside the loop. ----
1214 // As a side effect, reduces the amount of IV processing within the loop. ----
1215 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
1216 ----
1217 static bool hasHardUserWithinLoop(const Loop *L, const Instruction *I) { 0
1218 SmallPtrSet Visited; 0
1219 SmallVector WorkList; 0
1220 Visited.insert(I); 0
1221 WorkList.push_back(I); 0
1222 while (!WorkList.empty()) { 0
1223 const Instruction *Curr = WorkList.pop_back_val(); 0
1224 // This use is outside the loop, nothing to do. ----
1225 if (!L->contains(Curr)) 0
1226 continue; 0
1227 // Do we assume it is a "hard" use which will not be eliminated easily? ----
1228 if (Curr->mayHaveSideEffects()) 0
1229 return true; 0
1230 // Otherwise, add all its users to worklist. ----
1231 for (const auto *U : Curr->users()) { 0
1232 auto *UI = cast(U); 0
1233 if (Visited.insert(UI).second) 0
1234 WorkList.push_back(UI); 0
1235 } ----
1236 } ----
1237 return false; 0
1238 } 0
1239 ----
1240 // Collect information about PHI nodes which can be transformed in ----
1241 // rewriteLoopExitValues. ----
1242 struct RewritePhi { ----
1243 PHINode *PN; // For which PHI node is this replacement? ----
1244 unsigned Ith; // For which incoming value? ----
1245 const SCEV *ExpansionSCEV; // The SCEV of the incoming value we are rewriting. ----
1246 Instruction *ExpansionPoint; // Where we'd like to expand that SCEV? ----
1247 bool HighCost; // Is this expansion a high-cost? ----
1248 ----
1249 RewritePhi(PHINode *P, unsigned I, const SCEV *Val, Instruction *ExpansionPt, 0
1250 bool H) ----
1251 : PN(P), Ith(I), ExpansionSCEV(Val), ExpansionPoint(ExpansionPt), 0
1252 HighCost(H) {} 0
1253 }; ----
1254 ----
1255 // Check whether it is possible to delete the loop after rewriting exit ----
1256 // value. If it is possible, ignore ReplaceExitValue and do rewriting ----
1257 // aggressively. ----
1258 static bool canLoopBeDeleted(Loop *L, SmallVector &RewritePhiSet) { 0
1259 BasicBlock *Preheader = L->getLoopPreheader(); 0
1260 // If there is no preheader, the loop will not be deleted. ----
1261 if (!Preheader) 0
1262 return false; 0
1263 ----
1264 // In LoopDeletion pass Loop can be deleted when ExitingBlocks.size() > 1. ----
1265 // We obviate multiple ExitingBlocks case for simplicity. ----
1266 // TODO: If we see testcase with multiple ExitingBlocks can be deleted ----
1267 // after exit value rewriting, we can enhance the logic here. ----
1268 SmallVector ExitingBlocks; 0
1269 L->getExitingBlocks(ExitingBlocks); 0
1270 SmallVector ExitBlocks; 0
1271 L->getUniqueExitBlocks(ExitBlocks); 0
1272 if (ExitBlocks.size() != 1 || ExitingBlocks.size() != 1) 0
1273 return false; 0
1274 ----
1275 BasicBlock *ExitBlock = ExitBlocks[0]; 0
1276 BasicBlock::iterator BI = ExitBlock->begin(); 0
1277 while (PHINode *P = dyn_cast(BI)) { 0
1278 Value *Incoming = P->getIncomingValueForBlock(ExitingBlocks[0]); 0
1279 ----
1280 // If the Incoming value of P is found in RewritePhiSet, we know it ----
1281 // could be rewritten to use a loop invariant value in transformation ----
1282 // phase later. Skip it in the loop invariant check below. ----
1283 bool found = false; 0
1284 for (const RewritePhi &Phi : RewritePhiSet) { 0
1285 unsigned i = Phi.Ith; 0
1286 if (Phi.PN == P && (Phi.PN)->getIncomingValue(i) == Incoming) { 0
1287 found = true; 0
1288 break; 0
1289 } ----
1290 } ----
1291 ----
1292 Instruction *I; ----
1293 if (!found && (I = dyn_cast(Incoming))) 0
1294 if (!L->hasLoopInvariantOperands(I)) 0
1295 return false; 0
1296 ----
1297 ++BI; 0
1298 } 0
1299 ----
1300 for (auto *BB : L->blocks()) 0
1301 if (llvm::any_of(*BB, [](Instruction &I) { 0
1302 return I.mayHaveSideEffects(); 0
1303 })) ----
1304 return false; 0
1305 ----
1306 return true; 0
1307 } 0
1308 ----
1309 /// Checks if it is safe to call InductionDescriptor::isInductionPHI for \p Phi, ----
1310 /// and returns true if this Phi is an induction phi in the loop. When ----
1311 /// isInductionPHI returns true, \p ID will be also be set by isInductionPHI. ----
1312 static bool checkIsIndPhi(PHINode *Phi, Loop *L, ScalarEvolution *SE, 0
1313 InductionDescriptor &ID) { ----
1314 if (!Phi) 0
1315 return false; 0
1316 if (!L->getLoopPreheader()) 0
1317 return false; 0
1318 if (Phi->getParent() != L->getHeader()) 0
1319 return false; 0
1320 return InductionDescriptor::isInductionPHI(Phi, L, SE, ID); 0
1321 } ----
1322 ----
1323 int llvm::rewriteLoopExitValues(Loop *L, LoopInfo *LI, TargetLibraryInfo *TLI, 0
1324 ScalarEvolution *SE, ----
1325 const TargetTransformInfo *TTI, ----
1326 SCEVExpander &Rewriter, DominatorTree *DT, ----
1327 ReplaceExitVal ReplaceExitValue, ----
1328 SmallVector &DeadInsts) { ----
1329 // Check a pre-condition. ----
1330 assert(L->isRecursivelyLCSSAForm(*DT, *LI) && 0
1331 "Indvars did not preserve LCSSA!"); ----
1332 ----
1333 SmallVector ExitBlocks; 0
1334 L->getUniqueExitBlocks(ExitBlocks); 0
1335 ----
1336 SmallVector RewritePhiSet; 0
1337 // Find all values that are computed inside the loop, but used outside of it. ----
1338 // Because of LCSSA, these values will only occur in LCSSA PHI Nodes. Scan ----
1339 // the exit blocks of the loop to find them. ----
1340 for (BasicBlock *ExitBB : ExitBlocks) { 0
1341 // If there are no PHI nodes in this exit block, then no values defined ----
1342 // inside the loop are used on this path, skip it. ----
1343 PHINode *PN = dyn_cast(ExitBB->begin()); 0
1344 if (!PN) continue; 0
1345 ----
1346 unsigned NumPreds = PN->getNumIncomingValues(); 0
1347 ----
1348 // Iterate over all of the PHI nodes. ----
1349 BasicBlock::iterator BBI = ExitBB->begin(); 0
1350 while ((PN = dyn_cast(BBI++))) { 0
1351 if (PN->use_empty()) 0
1352 continue; // dead use, don't replace it 0
1353 ----
1354 if (!SE->isSCEVable(PN->getType())) 0
1355 continue; 0
1356 ----
1357 // Iterate over all of the values in all the PHI nodes. ----
1358 for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumPreds; ++i) { 0
1359 // If the value being merged in is not integer or is not defined ----
1360 // in the loop, skip it. ----
1361 Value *InVal = PN->getIncomingValue(i); 0
1362 if (!isa(InVal)) 0
1363 continue; 0
1364 ----
1365 // If this pred is for a subloop, not L itself, skip it. ----
1366 if (LI->getLoopFor(PN->getIncomingBlock(i)) != L) 0
1367 continue; // The Block is in a subloop, skip it. 0
1368 ----
1369 // Check that InVal is defined in the loop. ----
1370 Instruction *Inst = cast(InVal); 0
1371 if (!L->contains(Inst)) 0
1372 continue; 0
1373 ----
1374 // Find exit values which are induction variables in the loop, and are ----
1375 // unused in the loop, with the only use being the exit block PhiNode, ----
1376 // and the induction variable update binary operator. ----
1377 // The exit value can be replaced with the final value when it is cheap ----
1378 // to do so. ----
1379 if (ReplaceExitValue == UnusedIndVarInLoop) { 0
1380 InductionDescriptor ID; 0
1381 PHINode *IndPhi = dyn_cast(Inst); 0
1382 if (IndPhi) { 0
1383 if (!checkIsIndPhi(IndPhi, L, SE, ID)) 0
1384 continue; 0
1385 // This is an induction PHI. Check that the only users are PHI ----
1386 // nodes, and induction variable update binary operators. ----
1387 if (llvm::any_of(Inst->users(), [&](User *U) { 0
1388 if (!isa(U) && !isa(U)) 0
1389 return true; 0
1390 BinaryOperator *B = dyn_cast(U); 0
1391 if (B && B != ID.getInductionBinOp()) 0
1392 return true; 0
1393 return false; 0
1394 })) ----
1395 continue; 0
1396 } else { ----
1397 // If it is not an induction phi, it must be an induction update ----
1398 // binary operator with an induction phi user. ----
1399 BinaryOperator *B = dyn_cast(Inst); 0
1400 if (!B) 0
1401 continue; 0
1402 if (llvm::any_of(Inst->users(), [&](User *U) { 0
1403 PHINode *Phi = dyn_cast(U); 0
1404 if (Phi != PN && !checkIsIndPhi(Phi, L, SE, ID)) 0
1405 return true; 0
1406 return false; 0
1407 })) ----
1408 continue; 0
1409 if (B != ID.getInductionBinOp()) 0
1410 continue; 0
1411 } ----
1412 } 0
1413 ----
1414 // Okay, this instruction has a user outside of the current loop ----
1415 // and varies predictably *inside* the loop. Evaluate the value it ----
1416 // contains when the loop exits, if possible. We prefer to start with ----
1417 // expressions which are true for all exits (so as to maximize ----
1418 // expression reuse by the SCEVExpander), but resort to per-exit ----
1419 // evaluation if that fails. ----
1420 const SCEV *ExitValue = SE->getSCEVAtScope(Inst, L->getParentLoop()); 0
1421 if (isa(ExitValue) || 0
1422 !SE->isLoopInvariant(ExitValue, L) || 0
1423 !Rewriter.isSafeToExpand(ExitValue)) { 0
1424 // TODO: This should probably be sunk into SCEV in some way; maybe a ----
1425 // getSCEVForExit(SCEV*, L, ExitingBB)? It can be generalized for ----
1426 // most SCEV expressions and other recurrence types (e.g. shift ----
1427 // recurrences). Is there existing code we can reuse? ----
1428 const SCEV *ExitCount = SE->getExitCount(L, PN->getIncomingBlock(i)); 0
1429 if (isa(ExitCount)) 0
1430 continue; 0
1431 if (auto *AddRec = dyn_cast(SE->getSCEV(Inst))) 0
1432 if (AddRec->getLoop() == L) 0
1433 ExitValue = AddRec->evaluateAtIteration(ExitCount, *SE); 0
1434 if (isa(ExitValue) || 0
1435 !SE->isLoopInvariant(ExitValue, L) || 0
1436 !Rewriter.isSafeToExpand(ExitValue)) 0
1437 continue; 0
1438 } ----
1439 ----
1440 // Computing the value outside of the loop brings no benefit if it is ----
1441 // definitely used inside the loop in a way which can not be optimized ----
1442 // away. Avoid doing so unless we know we have a value which computes ----
1443 // the ExitValue already. TODO: This should be merged into SCEV ----
1444 // expander to leverage its knowledge of existing expressions. ----
1445 if (ReplaceExitValue != AlwaysRepl && !isa(ExitValue) && 0
1446 !isa(ExitValue) && hasHardUserWithinLoop(L, Inst)) 0
1447 continue; 0
1448 ----
1449 // Check if expansions of this SCEV would count as being high cost. ----
1450 bool HighCost = Rewriter.isHighCostExpansion( 0
1451 ExitValue, L, SCEVCheapExpansionBudget, TTI, Inst); 0
1452 ----
1453 // Note that we must not perform expansions until after ----
1454 // we query *all* the costs, because if we perform temporary expansion ----
1455 // inbetween, one that we might not intend to keep, said expansion ----
1456 // *may* affect cost calculation of the the next SCEV's we'll query, ----
1457 // and next SCEV may errneously get smaller cost. ----
1458 ----
1459 // Collect all the candidate PHINodes to be rewritten. ----
1460 Instruction *InsertPt = ----
1461 (isa(Inst) || isa(Inst)) ? 0
1462 &*Inst->getParent()->getFirstInsertionPt() : Inst; 0
1463 RewritePhiSet.emplace_back(PN, i, ExitValue, InsertPt, HighCost); 0
1464 } ----
1465 } ----
1466 } ----
1467 ----
1468 // TODO: evaluate whether it is beneficial to change how we calculate ----
1469 // high-cost: if we have SCEV 'A' which we know we will expand, should we ----
1470 // calculate the cost of other SCEV's after expanding SCEV 'A', thus ----
1471 // potentially giving cost bonus to those other SCEV's? ----
1472 ----
1473 bool LoopCanBeDel = canLoopBeDeleted(L, RewritePhiSet); 0
1474 int NumReplaced = 0; 0
1475 ----
1476 // Transformation. ----
1477 for (const RewritePhi &Phi : RewritePhiSet) { 0
1478 PHINode *PN = Phi.PN; 0
1479 ----
1480 // Only do the rewrite when the ExitValue can be expanded cheaply. ----
1481 // If LoopCanBeDel is true, rewrite exit value aggressively. ----
1482 if ((ReplaceExitValue == OnlyCheapRepl || 0
1483 ReplaceExitValue == UnusedIndVarInLoop) && 0
1484 !LoopCanBeDel && Phi.HighCost) 0
1485 continue; 0
1486 ----
1487 Value *ExitVal = Rewriter.expandCodeFor( 0
1488 Phi.ExpansionSCEV, Phi.PN->getType(), Phi.ExpansionPoint); 0
1489 ----
1490 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "rewriteLoopExitValues: AfterLoopVal = " << *ExitVal 0
1491 << '\n' ----
1492 << " LoopVal = " << *(Phi.ExpansionPoint) << "\n"); ----
1493 ----
1494 #ifndef NDEBUG ----
1495 // If we reuse an instruction from a loop which is neither L nor one of ----
1496 // its containing loops, we end up breaking LCSSA form for this loop by ----
1497 // creating a new use of its instruction. ----
1498 if (auto *ExitInsn = dyn_cast(ExitVal)) 0
1499 if (auto *EVL = LI->getLoopFor(ExitInsn->getParent())) 0
1500 if (EVL != L) 0
1501 assert(EVL->contains(L) && "LCSSA breach detected!"); 0
1502 #endif ----
1503 ----
1504 NumReplaced++; 0
1505 Instruction *Inst = cast(PN->getIncomingValue(Phi.Ith)); 0
1506 PN->setIncomingValue(Phi.Ith, ExitVal); 0
1507 // It's necessary to tell ScalarEvolution about this explicitly so that ----
1508 // it can walk the def-use list and forget all SCEVs, as it may not be ----
1509 // watching the PHI itself. Once the new exit value is in place, there ----
1510 // may not be a def-use connection between the loop and every instruction ----
1511 // which got a SCEVAddRecExpr for that loop. ----
1512 SE->forgetValue(PN); 0
1513 ----
1514 // If this instruction is dead now, delete it. Don't do it now to avoid ----
1515 // invalidating iterators. ----
1516 if (isInstructionTriviallyDead(Inst, TLI)) 0
1517 DeadInsts.push_back(Inst); 0
1518 ----
1519 // Replace PN with ExitVal if that is legal and does not break LCSSA. ----
1520 if (PN->getNumIncomingValues() == 1 && 0
1521 LI->replacementPreservesLCSSAForm(PN, ExitVal)) { 0
1522 PN->replaceAllUsesWith(ExitVal); 0
1523 PN->eraseFromParent(); 0
1524 } ----
1525 } ----
1526 ----
1527 // The insertion point instruction may have been deleted; clear it out ----
1528 // so that the rewriter doesn't trip over it later. ----
1529 Rewriter.clearInsertPoint(); 0
1530 return NumReplaced; 0
1531 } 0
1532 ----
1533 /// Set weights for \p UnrolledLoop and \p RemainderLoop based on weights for ----
1534 /// \p OrigLoop. ----
1535 void llvm::setProfileInfoAfterUnrolling(Loop *OrigLoop, Loop *UnrolledLoop, 0
1536 Loop *RemainderLoop, uint64_t UF) { ----
1537 assert(UF > 0 && "Zero unrolled factor is not supported"); 0
1538 assert(UnrolledLoop != RemainderLoop && 0
1539 "Unrolled and Remainder loops are expected to distinct"); ----
1540 ----
1541 // Get number of iterations in the original scalar loop. ----
1542 unsigned OrigLoopInvocationWeight = 0; 0
1543 std::optional OrigAverageTripCount = ----
1544 getLoopEstimatedTripCount(OrigLoop, &OrigLoopInvocationWeight); 0
1545 if (!OrigAverageTripCount) 0
1546 return; 0
1547 ----
1548 // Calculate number of iterations in unrolled loop. ----
1549 unsigned UnrolledAverageTripCount = *OrigAverageTripCount / UF; 0
1550 // Calculate number of iterations for remainder loop. ----
1551 unsigned RemainderAverageTripCount = *OrigAverageTripCount % UF; 0
1552 ----
1553 setLoopEstimatedTripCount(UnrolledLoop, UnrolledAverageTripCount, 0
1554 OrigLoopInvocationWeight); ----
1555 setLoopEstimatedTripCount(RemainderLoop, RemainderAverageTripCount, 0
1556 OrigLoopInvocationWeight); ----
1557 } ----
1558 ----
1559 /// Utility that implements appending of loops onto a worklist. ----
1560 /// Loops are added in preorder (analogous for reverse postorder for trees), ----
1561 /// and the worklist is processed LIFO. ----
1562 template ----
1563 void llvm::appendReversedLoopsToWorklist( 0
1564 RangeT &&Loops, SmallPriorityWorklist &Worklist) { ----
1565 // We use an internal worklist to build up the preorder traversal without ----
1566 // recursion. ----
1567 SmallVector PreOrderLoops, PreOrderWorklist; 0
1568 ----
1569 // We walk the initial sequence of loops in reverse because we generally want ----
1570 // to visit defs before uses and the worklist is LIFO. ----
1571 for (Loop *RootL : Loops) { 0
1572 assert(PreOrderLoops.empty() && "Must start with an empty preorder walk."); 0
1573 assert(PreOrderWorklist.empty() && 0
1574 "Must start with an empty preorder walk worklist."); ----
1575 PreOrderWorklist.push_back(RootL); 0
1576 do { ----
1577 Loop *L = PreOrderWorklist.pop_back_val(); 0
1578 PreOrderWorklist.append(L->begin(), L->end()); 0
1579 PreOrderLoops.push_back(L); 0
1580 } while (!PreOrderWorklist.empty()); 0
1581 ----
1582 Worklist.insert(std::move(PreOrderLoops)); 0
1583 PreOrderLoops.clear(); 0
1584 } ----
1585 } 0
1586 ----
1587 template ----
1588 void llvm::appendLoopsToWorklist(RangeT &&Loops, 0
1589 SmallPriorityWorklist &Worklist) { ----
1590 appendReversedLoopsToWorklist(reverse(Loops), Worklist); 0
1591 } 0
1592 ----
1593 template void llvm::appendLoopsToWorklist &>( ----
1594 ArrayRef &Loops, SmallPriorityWorklist &Worklist); ----
1595 ----
1596 template void ----
1597 llvm::appendLoopsToWorklist(Loop &L, ----
1598 SmallPriorityWorklist &Worklist); ----
1599 ----
1600 void llvm::appendLoopsToWorklist(LoopInfo &LI, 0
1601 SmallPriorityWorklist &Worklist) { ----
1602 appendReversedLoopsToWorklist(LI, Worklist); 0
1603 } 0
1604 ----
1605 Loop *llvm::cloneLoop(Loop *L, Loop *PL, ValueToValueMapTy &VM, 0
1606 LoopInfo *LI, LPPassManager *LPM) { ----
1607 Loop &New = *LI->AllocateLoop(); 0
1608 if (PL) 0
1609 PL->addChildLoop(&New); 0
1610 else ----
1611 LI->addTopLevelLoop(&New); 0
1612 ----
1613 if (LPM) 0
1614 LPM->addLoop(New); 0
1615 ----
1616 // Add all of the blocks in L to the new loop. ----
1617 for (BasicBlock *BB : L->blocks()) 0
1618 if (LI->getLoopFor(BB) == L) 0
1619 New.addBasicBlockToLoop(cast(VM[BB]), *LI); 0
1620 ----
1621 // Add all of the subloops to the new loop. ----
1622 for (Loop *I : *L) 0
1623 cloneLoop(I, &New, VM, LI, LPM); 0
1624 ----
1625 return &New; 0
1626 } ----
1627 ----
1628 /// IR Values for the lower and upper bounds of a pointer evolution. We ----
1629 /// need to use value-handles because SCEV expansion can invalidate previously ----
1630 /// expanded values. Thus expansion of a pointer can invalidate the bounds for ----
1631 /// a previous one. ----
1632 struct PointerBounds { ----
1633 TrackingVH Start; ----
1634 TrackingVH End; ----
1635 }; ----
1636 ----
1637 /// Expand code for the lower and upper bound of the pointer group \p CG ----
1638 /// in \p TheLoop. \return the values for the bounds. ----
1639 static PointerBounds expandBounds(const RuntimeCheckingPtrGroup *CG, 0
1640 Loop *TheLoop, Instruction *Loc, ----
1641 SCEVExpander &Exp) { ----
1642 LLVMContext &Ctx = Loc->getContext(); 0
1643 Type *PtrArithTy = Type::getInt8PtrTy(Ctx, CG->AddressSpace); 0
1644 ----
1645 Value *Start = nullptr, *End = nullptr; 0
1646 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "LAA: Adding RT check for range:\n"); 0
1647 Start = Exp.expandCodeFor(CG->Low, PtrArithTy, Loc); 0
1648 End = Exp.expandCodeFor(CG->High, PtrArithTy, Loc); 0
1649 if (CG->NeedsFreeze) { 0
1650 IRBuilder<> Builder(Loc); 0
1651 Start = Builder.CreateFreeze(Start, Start->getName() + ".fr"); 0
1652 End = Builder.CreateFreeze(End, End->getName() + ".fr"); 0
1653 } 0
1654 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Start: " << *CG->Low << " End: " << *CG->High << "\n"); 0
1655 return {Start, End}; 0
1656 } ----
1657 ----
1658 /// Turns a collection of checks into a collection of expanded upper and ----
1659 /// lower bounds for both pointers in the check. ----
1660 static SmallVector, 4> ----
1661 expandBounds(const SmallVectorImpl &PointerChecks, Loop *L, 0
1662 Instruction *Loc, SCEVExpander &Exp) { ----
1663 SmallVector, 4> ChecksWithBounds; 0
1664 ----
1665 // Here we're relying on the SCEV Expander's cache to only emit code for the ----
1666 // same bounds once. ----
1667 transform(PointerChecks, std::back_inserter(ChecksWithBounds), 0
1668 [&](const RuntimePointerCheck &Check) { 0
1669 PointerBounds First = expandBounds(Check.first, L, Loc, Exp), 0
1670 Second = expandBounds(Check.second, L, Loc, Exp); 0
1671 return std::make_pair(First, Second); 0
1672 }); 0
1673 ----
1674 return ChecksWithBounds; 0
1675 } ----
1676 ----
1677 Value *llvm::addRuntimeChecks( 0
1678 Instruction *Loc, Loop *TheLoop, ----
1679 const SmallVectorImpl &PointerChecks, ----
1680 SCEVExpander &Exp) { ----
1681 // TODO: Move noalias annotation code from LoopVersioning here and share with LV if possible. ----
1682 // TODO: Pass RtPtrChecking instead of PointerChecks and SE separately, if possible ----
1683 auto ExpandedChecks = expandBounds(PointerChecks, TheLoop, Loc, Exp); 0
1684 ----
1685 LLVMContext &Ctx = Loc->getContext(); 0
1686 IRBuilder ChkBuilder(Ctx, ----
1687 Loc->getModule()->getDataLayout()); 0
1688 ChkBuilder.SetInsertPoint(Loc); 0
1689 // Our instructions might fold to a constant. ----
1690 Value *MemoryRuntimeCheck = nullptr; 0
1691 ----
1692 for (const auto &Check : ExpandedChecks) { 0
1693 const PointerBounds &A = Check.first, &B = Check.second; 0
1694 // Check if two pointers (A and B) conflict where conflict is computed as: ----
1695 // start(A) <= end(B) && start(B) <= end(A) ----
1696 unsigned AS0 = A.Start->getType()->getPointerAddressSpace(); 0
1697 unsigned AS1 = B.Start->getType()->getPointerAddressSpace(); 0
1698 ----
1699 assert((AS0 == B.End->getType()->getPointerAddressSpace()) && 0
1700 (AS1 == A.End->getType()->getPointerAddressSpace()) && ----
1701 "Trying to bounds check pointers with different address spaces"); ----
1702 ----
1703 Type *PtrArithTy0 = Type::getInt8PtrTy(Ctx, AS0); 0
1704 Type *PtrArithTy1 = Type::getInt8PtrTy(Ctx, AS1); 0
1705 ----
1706 Value *Start0 = ChkBuilder.CreateBitCast(A.Start, PtrArithTy0, "bc"); 0
1707 Value *Start1 = ChkBuilder.CreateBitCast(B.Start, PtrArithTy1, "bc"); 0
1708 Value *End0 = ChkBuilder.CreateBitCast(A.End, PtrArithTy1, "bc"); 0
1709 Value *End1 = ChkBuilder.CreateBitCast(B.End, PtrArithTy0, "bc"); 0
1710 ----
1711 // [A|B].Start points to the first accessed byte under base [A|B]. ----
1712 // [A|B].End points to the last accessed byte, plus one. ----
1713 // There is no conflict when the intervals are disjoint: ----
1714 // NoConflict = (B.Start >= A.End) || (A.Start >= B.End) ----
1715 // ----
1716 // bound0 = (B.Start < A.End) ----
1717 // bound1 = (A.Start < B.End) ----
1718 // IsConflict = bound0 & bound1 ----
1719 Value *Cmp0 = ChkBuilder.CreateICmpULT(Start0, End1, "bound0"); 0
1720 Value *Cmp1 = ChkBuilder.CreateICmpULT(Start1, End0, "bound1"); 0
1721 Value *IsConflict = ChkBuilder.CreateAnd(Cmp0, Cmp1, "found.conflict"); 0
1722 if (MemoryRuntimeCheck) { 0
1723 IsConflict = ----
1724 ChkBuilder.CreateOr(MemoryRuntimeCheck, IsConflict, "conflict.rdx"); 0
1725 } ----
1726 MemoryRuntimeCheck = IsConflict; 0
1727 } ----
1728 ----
1729 return MemoryRuntimeCheck; 0
1730 } 0
1731 ----
1732 Value *llvm::addDiffRuntimeChecks( 0
1733 Instruction *Loc, ArrayRef Checks, SCEVExpander &Expander, ----
1734 function_ref GetVF, unsigned IC) { ----
1735 ----
1736 LLVMContext &Ctx = Loc->getContext(); 0
1737 IRBuilder ChkBuilder(Ctx, ----
1738 Loc->getModule()->getDataLayout()); 0
1739 ChkBuilder.SetInsertPoint(Loc); 0
1740 // Our instructions might fold to a constant. ----
1741 Value *MemoryRuntimeCheck = nullptr; 0
1742 ----
1743 for (const auto &C : Checks) { 0
1744 Type *Ty = C.SinkStart->getType(); 0
1745 // Compute VF * IC * AccessSize. ----
1746 auto *VFTimesUFTimesSize = ----
1747 ChkBuilder.CreateMul(GetVF(ChkBuilder, Ty->getScalarSizeInBits()), 0
1748 ConstantInt::get(Ty, IC * C.AccessSize)); 0
1749 Value *Sink = Expander.expandCodeFor(C.SinkStart, Ty, Loc); 0
1750 Value *Src = Expander.expandCodeFor(C.SrcStart, Ty, Loc); 0
1751 if (C.NeedsFreeze) { 0
1752 IRBuilder<> Builder(Loc); 0
1753 Sink = Builder.CreateFreeze(Sink, Sink->getName() + ".fr"); 0
1754 Src = Builder.CreateFreeze(Src, Src->getName() + ".fr"); 0
1755 } 0
1756 Value *Diff = ChkBuilder.CreateSub(Sink, Src); 0
1757 Value *IsConflict = ----
1758 ChkBuilder.CreateICmpULT(Diff, VFTimesUFTimesSize, "diff.check"); 0
1759 ----
1760 if (MemoryRuntimeCheck) { 0
1761 IsConflict = ----
1762 ChkBuilder.CreateOr(MemoryRuntimeCheck, IsConflict, "conflict.rdx"); 0
1763 } ----
1764 MemoryRuntimeCheck = IsConflict; 0
1765 } ----
1766 ----
1767 return MemoryRuntimeCheck; 0
1768 } 0
1769 ----
1770 std::optional ----
1771 llvm::hasPartialIVCondition(const Loop &L, unsigned MSSAThreshold, 0
1772 const MemorySSA &MSSA, AAResults &AA) { ----
1773 auto *TI = dyn_cast(L.getHeader()->getTerminator()); 0
1774 if (!TI || !TI->isConditional()) 0
1775 return {}; 0
1776 ----
1777 auto *CondI = dyn_cast(TI->getCondition()); 0
1778 // The case with the condition outside the loop should already be handled ----
1779 // earlier. ----
1780 if (!CondI || !L.contains(CondI)) 0
1781 return {}; 0
1782 ----
1783 SmallVector InstToDuplicate; 0
1784 InstToDuplicate.push_back(CondI); 0
1785 ----
1786 SmallVector WorkList; 0
1787 WorkList.append(CondI->op_begin(), CondI->op_end()); 0
1788 ----
1789 SmallVector AccessesToCheck; 0
1790 SmallVector AccessedLocs; 0
1791 while (!WorkList.empty()) { 0
1792 Instruction *I = dyn_cast(WorkList.pop_back_val()); 0
1793 if (!I || !L.contains(I)) 0
1794 continue; 0
1795 ----
1796 // TODO: support additional instructions. ----
1797 if (!isa(I) && !isa(I)) 0
1798 return {}; 0
1799 ----
1800 // Do not duplicate volatile and atomic loads. ----
1801 if (auto *LI = dyn_cast(I)) 0
1802 if (LI->isVolatile() || LI->isAtomic()) 0
1803 return {}; 0
1804 ----
1805 InstToDuplicate.push_back(I); 0
1806 if (MemoryAccess *MA = MSSA.getMemoryAccess(I)) { 0
1807 if (auto *MemUse = dyn_cast_or_null(MA)) { 0
1808 // Queue the defining access to check for alias checks. ----
1809 AccessesToCheck.push_back(MemUse->getDefiningAccess()); 0
1810 AccessedLocs.push_back(MemoryLocation::get(I)); 0
1811 } else { ----
1812 // MemoryDefs may clobber the location or may be atomic memory ----
1813 // operations. Bail out. ----
1814 return {}; 0
1815 } ----
1816 } ----
1817 WorkList.append(I->op_begin(), I->op_end()); 0
1818 } ----
1819 ----
1820 if (InstToDuplicate.empty()) 0
1821 return {}; 0
1822 ----
1823 SmallVector ExitingBlocks; 0
1824 L.getExitingBlocks(ExitingBlocks); 0
1825 auto HasNoClobbersOnPath = ----
1826 [&L, &AA, &AccessedLocs, &ExitingBlocks, &InstToDuplicate, 0
1827 MSSAThreshold](BasicBlock *Succ, BasicBlock *Header, ----
1828 SmallVector AccessesToCheck) ----
1829 -> std::optional { 0
1830 IVConditionInfo Info; 0
1831 // First, collect all blocks in the loop that are on a patch from Succ ----
1832 // to the header. ----
1833 SmallVector WorkList; 0
1834 WorkList.push_back(Succ); 0
1835 WorkList.push_back(Header); 0
1836 SmallPtrSet Seen; 0
1837 Seen.insert(Header); 0
1838 Info.PathIsNoop &= 0
1839 all_of(*Header, [](Instruction &I) { return !I.mayHaveSideEffects(); }); 0
1840 ----
1841 while (!WorkList.empty()) { 0
1842 BasicBlock *Current = WorkList.pop_back_val(); 0
1843 if (!L.contains(Current)) 0
1844 continue; 0
1845 const auto &SeenIns = Seen.insert(Current); 0
1846 if (!SeenIns.second) 0
1847 continue; 0
1848 ----
1849 Info.PathIsNoop &= all_of( 0
1850 *Current, [](Instruction &I) { return !I.mayHaveSideEffects(); }); 0
1851 WorkList.append(succ_begin(Current), succ_end(Current)); 0
1852 } ----
1853 ----
1854 // Require at least 2 blocks on a path through the loop. This skips ----
1855 // paths that directly exit the loop. ----
1856 if (Seen.size() < 2) 0
1857 return {}; 0
1858 ----
1859 // Next, check if there are any MemoryDefs that are on the path through ----
1860 // the loop (in the Seen set) and they may-alias any of the locations in ----
1861 // AccessedLocs. If that is the case, they may modify the condition and ----
1862 // partial unswitching is not possible. ----
1863 SmallPtrSet SeenAccesses; 0
1864 while (!AccessesToCheck.empty()) { 0
1865 MemoryAccess *Current = AccessesToCheck.pop_back_val(); 0
1866 auto SeenI = SeenAccesses.insert(Current); 0
1867 if (!SeenI.second || !Seen.contains(Current->getBlock())) 0
1868 continue; 0
1869 ----
1870 // Bail out if exceeded the threshold. ----
1871 if (SeenAccesses.size() >= MSSAThreshold) 0
1872 return {}; 0
1873 ----
1874 // MemoryUse are read-only accesses. ----
1875 if (isa(Current)) 0
1876 continue; 0
1877 ----
1878 // For a MemoryDef, check if is aliases any of the location feeding ----
1879 // the original condition. ----
1880 if (auto *CurrentDef = dyn_cast(Current)) { 0
1881 if (any_of(AccessedLocs, [&AA, CurrentDef](MemoryLocation &Loc) { 0
1882 return isModSet( 0
1883 AA.getModRefInfo(CurrentDef->getMemoryInst(), Loc)); 0
1884 })) ----
1885 return {}; 0
1886 } ----
1887 ----
1888 for (Use &U : Current->uses()) 0
1889 AccessesToCheck.push_back(cast(U.getUser())); 0
1890 } ----
1891 ----
1892 // We could also allow loops with known trip counts without mustprogress, ----
1893 // but ScalarEvolution may not be available. ----
1894 Info.PathIsNoop &= isMustProgress(&L); 0
1895 ----
1896 // If the path is considered a no-op so far, check if it reaches a ----
1897 // single exit block without any phis. This ensures no values from the ----
1898 // loop are used outside of the loop. ----
1899 if (Info.PathIsNoop) { 0
1900 for (auto *Exiting : ExitingBlocks) { 0
1901 if (!Seen.contains(Exiting)) 0
1902 continue; 0
1903 for (auto *Succ : successors(Exiting)) { 0
1904 if (L.contains(Succ)) 0
1905 continue; 0
1906 ----
1907 Info.PathIsNoop &= Succ->phis().empty() && 0
1908 (!Info.ExitForPath || Info.ExitForPath == Succ); 0
1909 if (!Info.PathIsNoop) 0
1910 break; 0
1911 assert((!Info.ExitForPath || Info.ExitForPath == Succ) && 0
1912 "cannot have multiple exit blocks"); ----
1913 Info.ExitForPath = Succ; 0
1914 } ----
1915 } ----
1916 } ----
1917 if (!Info.ExitForPath) 0
1918 Info.PathIsNoop = false; 0
1919 ----
1920 Info.InstToDuplicate = InstToDuplicate; 0
1921 return Info; 0
1922 }; 0
1923 ----
1924 // If we branch to the same successor, partial unswitching will not be ----
1925 // beneficial. ----
1926 if (TI->getSuccessor(0) == TI->getSuccessor(1)) 0
1927 return {}; 0
1928 ----
1929 if (auto Info = HasNoClobbersOnPath(TI->getSuccessor(0), L.getHeader(), 0
1930 AccessesToCheck)) { 0
1931 Info->KnownValue = ConstantInt::getTrue(TI->getContext()); 0
1932 return Info; 0
1933 } 0
1934 if (auto Info = HasNoClobbersOnPath(TI->getSuccessor(1), L.getHeader(), 0
1935 AccessesToCheck)) { 0
1936 Info->KnownValue = ConstantInt::getFalse(TI->getContext()); 0
1937 return Info; 0
1938 } 0
1939 ----
1940 return {}; 0
1941 } 0
